    "body": "## Steps to reproduce\r\n1. Go to soundcloud.com (or other websites e.g. youtube.com/tmall.com)\r\n2. Play a soundtrack and scroll down on the page. (on youtube.com/tmall.com scroll the pages).\r\n3. Notice the bottom bar.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\nThe bottom bar should always remain displayed on the screen when scrolling, as it does on Fenix/Chrome.\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\nOn soundcloud.com, the bottom bar is partially dismissed when the dynamic toolbar and trash icon are displayed. (On Fenix/Chrome the bottom bar remains displayed at all times).\r\n\r\nOn youtube.com/tmall.com, the bottom bar is dismissed when the dynamic toolbar and trash icon are displayed. (The same behavior is present on Fenix. On Chrome, the bottom bar remains displayed at all times).\r\n\r\nRegression after #5452.\r\nRelates to issue https://github.com/mozilla-mobile/focus-android/issues/5456 which was updated and closed. This ticket was opened to follow up on the comment from the mentioned issue #5456.\r\n\r\n### Device information\r\n* Android device: Huawei P9 Lite  (Android 8).\r\n* Focus version: Debug build from main 10/26 (95.0 build 11 GV - 95.0a1-20211023211445).\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/89388888/138881289-827cc46e-fe7c-407a-ba81-1346ffd93197.mp4\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/89388888/138892343-e01b15f5-1004-4d16-b4c9-790b478fcd4d.mp4\r\n\r\n\r\n",
